Morphology and anatomy.
Cormus delicate, formed by large, irregular, loosely anastomosed and ramified tubes with one or several oscula at the end of larger tubes (water-collecting tubes; 
Fig 2A
). Aquiferous system asconoid. The skeleton is composed of two size categories of tetractines (
Fig 2B
), of which the larger is rare, and by small rare triactines.

Tetractines I
. Large. Regular (equiangular and equiradiate) or sagittal. Actines are conical with sharp tips (
Fig 2C
). The sagittal spicules sometimes have curved paired actines. The apical actine is cylindrical, very long, sharp, smooth and frequently curved but straight apical actines are also present (
Fig 2C
). Size: 162.0–218.7/ 16.2–27.0 µm (basal), 75.0–150.0/ 5.0–15.0 µm (apical).
